\left| \begin{array}{ccc} e^x & e^{2x} & ... & e^{nx}\\ e^x & 2e^{2x} & ...& ne^{nx} \\ e^x & 4e^{2x} &... & n^2e^{nx}\\ ...&...&...&...\\ e^x&2^{n-1}e^{2x} & ... & n^{n-1}e^{nx}\end{array} \right| 
\left| \begin{array}{ccc} 1 & 1 & ... & 1\\ 1 & 2 & ...& n \\ 1 & 4 &... & n^2\\ ...&...&...&...\\ 1 &2^{n-1} & ... & n^{n-1}\end{array} \right|
\left| \begin{array}{ccc} 1 & 1 & ... & 1\\ 1 & 2 & ...& n \\ 1 & 4 &... & n^2\\ ...&...&...&...\\ 1 &2^{n-1} & ... & n^{n-1}\end{array} \right|=0!*1!*2!*...*(n-1)!
0!1!2!...n!=(1)*(1*2)*(1*2*3)*...(1*2*3*...*n)=1^n*2^{n-1}*3^{n-2}*...*(n-1)^2*n
(\alpha_1,\alpha_2,\ldots,\alpha_n)=(1,2,\ldots,n)
\det(M)=\prod_{1\leq i<j\leq n} (\alpha_j-\alpha_i),
